    "body": "It's actually worse than not being able to use the ethers and waffle plugins. The way Buidler is architected seems to not be compatible \\*at all\\* with yarn v2 + typescript.\r\n\r\nIf I run `yarn buidler compile` in a yarn v2 project, I'm given the default response:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n? What do you want to do? … \r\n❯ Create a sample project\r\n  Create an empty buidler.config.js\r\n  Quit\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut if I copy-and-paste the same source code into a yarn v1 project, `yarn builder compile` successfully compiles the contract:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nCompiling...\r\nDownloading compiler version 0.6.8\r\nCompiled 1 contract successfully\r\n✨  Done in 4.12s.\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor the record, this is my `tsconfig.json`:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\r\n    \"lib\": [\"es5\"],\r\n    \"module\": \"commonjs\",\r\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\r\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\r\n    \"target\": \"es5\",\r\n\r\n    \"noImplicitAny\": true,\r\n    \"strict\": true,\r\n\r\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\r\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\r\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\r\n\r\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true\r\n  },\r\n  \"files\": [\r\n    \"./buidler.config.ts\",\r\n    \"./node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler-ethers/src/type-extensions.d.ts\",\r\n    \"./node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler-waffle/src/type-extensions.d.ts\"\r\n  ],\r\n  \"include\": [\"./scripts\", \"./test\"]\r\n}\r\n```",
