    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Well, with over [38.5k](https://github.com/yarnpkg/yarn) stars, an active and responsive community on Discord and killer features like [workspaces](https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/docs/workspaces/), it's hard for Yarn to fade away any time soon. Not impossible, but hard.\r\n\r\nAs v2 is concerned, it looks super promising. The \"node_modules\" folder is a sunk cost we got used to, yet I suspect that everyone would agree that life would be better without it. Supporting yarn v2 is a small step towards a better developer experience in the big, vivid world of open-source, not just JavaScript or Ethereum.\r\n\r\nWhat incompatibilities I found in Buidler:\r\n\r\n1. The \"buidler.config.ts\" file is not recognised when yarn v2 finds and executes buidler from pnp\r\n2. The ethers and waffle plugins cannot be used because their type extensions cannot be added to \"tsconfig.json\"\r\n\r\nI'll keep reporting things here as I discover them.",
